## Islamic Content License

The Islamic content (Al-Quran text, translations, hadith, and religious materials)
included in this application are sourced from authenticated Islamic sources and
are provided for educational and religious purposes only.

### Al-Quran
- The text of the Holy Quran is in the public domain
- Translations are sourced from trusted translators
- Audio recitations are used with proper licensing

### Hadith
- Hadith collections from authenticated sources
- Provided for educational purposes only
- Not for commercial use

### Conditions for Islamic Content
1. Content must not be altered or misrepresented
2. Proper attribution must be maintained
3. Content should be used respectfully
4. Not to be used for any purpose that contradicts Islamic principles

